body:
Errors for [E0401](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0401) supply incorrect or otherwise lacking hints in many cases.  Some examples follow.  All exploration was done via the playground stable channel v1.47.0.

#### Example 1
[Inner `fn`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=c1b0186c0449e04d76934c254654524d)
```rust
fn outer<T>() {
    fn inner<U: T>() {}
}
```
Result:
```
help: try using a local generic parameter instead: `inner<U: T<T>`
```

The angle brackets aren't balanced.

#### Example 2
[Inner `type`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=904f09a8daaa0c4e2150256bb0477b4b)
```rust
fn outer<T>() {
    type V = Option<T>;
}
```
Result:
```
1 | fn outer<T>() {
  |    ----- - type parameter from outer function
  |    |
  |    try adding a local generic parameter in this method instead
```

Isn't it telling me to add what is already there?  (It's possible I just don't understand this message.  However see the next example.)  The error is the same for inner `struct`s.

[Inner `struct` following inner `fn`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=54dbed2e3c111a461a3d7432d750b1d0)
#### Example 3
```rust
fn outer<T>() {
    fn inner<U: T>() {}
    struct W { X: T }
}
```
Result:
```
1 | fn outer<T>() {
  |          - type parameter from outer function
2 |     fn inner<U: T>() {}
  |        ----- try adding a local generic parameter in this method instead
```

Now it's suggesting I add to the sibling `fn`, and not the containing `fn`.  (The error is the same for inner `type`s.)

#### Example 4
[Inner `type` following _commented out_ inner `fn`](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=fa47125bc6fbdd4e169c19ffa595d38f)
```rust
fn outer<T>() {
//  fn inner<U: T>() {}
    type V = Option<T>;
}
```
Result:
```
1 | fn outer<T>() {
  |          - type parameter from outer function
2 | //  fn inner<U: T>() {}
  |        ----- try adding a local generic parameter in this method instead
```

And now it's telling me to add a parameter to a _commented out_ function!
